<title>vStreamBufferDelete</title>
<indexterm><primary>vStreamBufferDelete</primary></indexterm>

<para><link linkend="_stream__buffer_8h_source">stream_buffer.h</link></para>

<para><literallayout>
void vStreamBufferDelete( StreamBufferHandle_t xStreamBuffer );
</literallayout></para>

<para>Deletes a stream buffer that was previously created using a call to xStreamBufferCreate() or xStreamBufferCreateStatic(). If the stream buffer was created using dynamic memory (that is, by xStreamBufferCreate()), then the allocated memory is freed.</para>

<para>A stream buffer handle must not be used after the stream buffer has been deleted.</para>

